browser-skill
Copyright (c) 2026 cyh-skill

This product is a derivative / fusion work built on top of two upstream projects.
Grateful attribution to both:

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
1) web-access  —  https://github.com/eze-is/web-access
   Author: 一泽Eze
   License: MIT

   browser-skill directly derives from web-access. Carried forward largely
   as-is: the CDP-proxy architecture and HTTP API, browser auto-discovery
   (browser-discovery.mjs), dependency check (check-deps.mjs), local
   bookmark/history search (find-url.mjs), site-pattern matching
   (match-site.mjs), the "browsing philosophy" and tool-selection guidance
   in SKILL.md, and several site-pattern notes (x.com, xiaohongshu.com,
   goofish.com, zhipin.com) and the v2.5.3 POST-body migration doc.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
2) chrome-use  —  https://github.com/leeguooooo/chrome-use
   Author: leeguooooo
   License: Apache License 2.0

   Ideas incorporated (re-implemented independently in JS for this skill's
   CDP-proxy / extension-bridge, not copied from chrome-use's Rust source):
   multi-session isolation with colored tab groups, humanized input
   (curved cursor trajectory + variable typing cadence), network
   interception (block / mock / rewrite), and the browser-extension bridge
   connection approach.
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Original additions by cyh-skill: the /extract structured site-adapter
endpoint and adapters/ modules, run-adapter.mjs, the self-contained
WebSocket server in ext-bridge.mjs, the MV3 bridge extension, and
zhihu.com / mp.weixin.qq.com site patterns and adapters.
